<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>General Marshall to Mr.
                            Walter S. Robertson, at Peiping</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v10</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d129</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">129</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-09-29T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-09-29T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-09-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-09-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="129" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Walter S. Robertson</persName>, at Peiping</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-09-29">29 September
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1581. Concur in your recommendation to authorize American member to record
                    testimony of the two Nationalist witnesses Reurad 1053.<note n="6" xml:id="d129fn6">September 28, <ref target="#pg_242">p. 242</ref>.</note>
                    Chou En-lai being informed of this action this date paraphrased as follows:</p>
                <pb facs="0253" n="243" xml:id="pg_243"/>
                <p>“To preclude further delay in the investigation of the Anping incident, Mr.
                    Robertson has been directed to instruct the American member of the team
                    investigating this matter to complete taking the testimony of remaining
                    witnesses, and if required by circumstances, submit his own report in order to
                    conclude his connections with investigating team.”</p>
            </div>
        </body>
